    "content": "<div class=\"entry-content\">\n<p>\n<img width=\"625\" height=\"333\" src=\"http://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Ablaze-625x333.png\" class=\"attachment-medium wp-post-image\" alt=\"Ablaze\"></p>\n<p>I'm not sure what I'd do with <a onclick=\"javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/pat.theorigin.net/2011/09/02/ablaze-js/');\" href=\"http://pat.theorigin.net/2011/09/02/ablaze-js/\">Ablaze.js</a>, a JavaScript library by Patrick Gunderson, but the results are sexy. Play around with the app <a onclick=\"javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/theorigin.net/ablazejs');\" href=\"http://theorigin.net/ablazejs\">here</a>. [via @<a onclick=\"javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/twitter.com/JeffClark');\" href=\"https://twitter.com/JeffClark\">jeffclark</a>]</p>\n<div class=\"clear-line\"></div>\n</div>"
